label: legitimate
name: Wesley Wong
text:
Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine has made a name for itself with an outlet at Pasir Ris Mall, and the long queues outside are a testament to its popularity and quality. Specializing in authentic Chinese cuisine, the restaurant consistently delivers top-notch food that leaves diners coming back for more.

One standout feature of Xiang Xiang is their approach to serving rice. Instead of the usual bowls, they serve their signature rice straight from an entire rice cooker placed on your table. This not only ensures the rice stays warm throughout the meal but also adds a unique touch to the dining experience. A custom tray is provided to hold the rice cooker, making it both practical and charming.

Xiang Xiang‚Äôs menu boasts three signature dishes that truly shine. The Sour and Spicy Fish is a must-try‚Äîeven surpasses the version offered by the nearby Taier restaurant, which is renowned for the same dish. The balance of tangy, spicy flavors with tender fish is simply unbeatable. Equally impressive are the Angus Beef Stir-Fry and the Stir-Fried Pork, both of which are aromatic and flavorful. However, they can be a bit oily, which may not suit everyone‚Äôs preference.

Beyond the signature items, the rest of the menu holds its own with a variety of delicious dishes that showcase the bold and spicy flavors characteristic of Hunan cuisine.

To top it all off, Xiang Xiang adds a sweet finishing touch by offering free ice cream after your meal, much like the popular Haidilao chain. It‚Äôs a delightful way to cleanse your palate and end the dining experience on a high note.

Overall, Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine offers exceptional food, a unique dining setup, and thoughtful extras, making it well worth a visit for fans of authentic Chinese cuisine.
title: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine @ Pasir Ris Mall

label: legitimate
name: Rianne
reviewContext/Recommended dishes: Golden Broth Sour and Spicy Fish
text:
This has gotta be my new favourite China food place in Pasir Ris Mall. Yes, move over Tai Er.

Recommend you try:
- Suan cai yu (Prefer this over Taier for taste and price lol
- La zi ji (Spicy chicken - so GOOD especially with the lotus roots. Doesn't taste like your usual oily laziji that has fried chilli)
- Stir fried Eggplants (HUGE portion)
- Tofu bites (addictive dip)

Skip:
- Cold noodles if you like the chewy type because these aren't the usual chewy kind but more like Jelly, I guess? Unless you fancy the kind that disintegrates when you pick it up with chopsticks.

Also, free flow ice cream and snacks. Always a +. Food's and service was great, will be back many times for more!

Only negative? Place can feel a little noisy depending on where you're seated.
title: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine @ Pasir Ris Mall

Price is on a higher side though as this came out about $100+ with gst&scv charge. But its for 4 pax so i guess still okay..

Wouldnt mind coming back again!
